ll, Škotska, United Kingdom","Lochbuie, Argyll, Scotland":"Lochbuie, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"cs":{"about 1300–":"okolo 1300–Zesnulá","1300–Female":"1300–Zesnulá","1280–1330":"1280–1330","1324–1405":"1324–1405","1330–1408":"1330–1408","–Male":"Zesnulý","1324":"1324","1300":"1300","about 1323":"okolo 1323","1330":"1330","about 1300":"okolo 1300","about 1330":"okolo 1330","1408":"1408","1280":"1280","1405":"1405","Knapdale, Argyll, Scotland":"Knapdale, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Argyll, Skotsko, United Kingdom","Lochbuie, Argyll, Scotland":"Lochbuie, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"da":{"about 1300–":"omkring 1300–Afdød","1300–Female":"1300–Afdød","1280–1330":"1280–1330","1324–1405":"1324–1405","1330–1408":"1330–1408","–Male":"Afdød","1324":"1324","1300":"1300","about 1323":"omkring 1323","1330":"1330","about 1300":"omkring 1300","about 1330":"omkring 1330","1408":"1408","1280":"1280","1405":"1405","Knapdale, Argyll, Scotland":"Knapdale, Argyll, Skotland","Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Argyll, Skotland, United Kingdom","Lochbuie, Argyll, Scotland":"Lochbuie, Argyll, Skotland","Scotland":"Skotland"},"nl":{"about 1300–":"circa 1300–Overleden","1300–Female":"1300–Overleden","1280–1330":"1280–1330","1324–1405":"1324–1405","1330–1408":"1330–1408","–Male":"Overleden","1324":"1324","1300":"1300","about 1323":"circa 1323","1330":"1330","about 1300":"circa 1300","about 1330":"circa 1330","1408":"1408","1280":"1280","1405":"1405","Knapdale, Argyll, Scotland":"Knapdale, Argyll, Schotland","Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Argyll, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Lochbuie, Argyll, Scotland":"Lochbuie, Argyll, Schotland","Scotland":"Schotland"},"en":{"about 1300–":"about 1300–Deceased","1300–Female":"1300–Deceased","1280–1330":"1280–1330","1324–1405":"1324–1405","1330–1408":"1330–1408","–Male":"Deceased","1324":"1324","1300":"1300","about 1323":"about 1323","1330":"1330","about 1300":"about 1300","about 1330":"about 1330","1408":"1408","1280":"1280","1405":"1405","Knapdale, Argyll, Scotland":"Knapdale, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom","Lochbuie, Argyll, Scotland":"Lochbuie, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cumming","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish (of Norman origin): most probably a habitational name from Bosc-Benard-Commin in Eure, France. This place lies on the edge of the Forêt de Rouvray, near Rouen, in the heart of the district from which came numerous Domesday barons, and so is much more likely to be the source of the name than Comines in Nord. The name is also possibly derived from the personal name <i>Cumin</i>, which is found in Norfolk, Lincolnshire, and Yorkshire in the 12th and 13th centuries and may be of Breton origin, according to Reaney. Compare Old Breton <i>Cunmin</i>, which also appears as <i>Cumin</i>, and is from <i>con-</i> ‘hound’ with an uncertain second element, perhaps the <i>min</i> ‘edge’ which is found in other personal names.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Cuimín</b> (or <b>Ó Cuimín</b>) ‘son (or ‘descendant’) of <i>Cuimín</i>’, a personal name formed from a diminutive of <i>cam</i> ‘crooked’. There was a 7th-century abbot of Iona named <i>Cumin</i>. In Scotland, this Irish surname became confused with the Norman name.","History: A notable bearer of the Norman surname is Wilhelmus Comyn, Bishop of Durham, who came north to Scotland with King David I in 1124 and was appointed Chancellor of Scotland. He established his nephew Richard in Tynedale and Roxburghshire, and Richard also rose to be Chancellor of Scotland. The Comyn or Cumming family gained the earldoms of Buchan and Menteith and rose to be the most powerful noble family in Scotland in the century before the rise of King Robert Bruce."],"variants":[{"name":"Cowman","meanings":["Scottish (of Norman origin): variant of   Cumming  ."]},{"name":"Coman","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Romanian Vasile, Cornel, Mihaela, Nicolae, Sorin, Viorel.","Irish (Tipperary and Waterford): shortened form of <b>Mac Cuimín</b> or <b>Ó Cuimín</b>, see   Cumming  .","English (Norfolk): variant of   Common  ."]},{"name":"Cummings","meanings":["Scottish and English (of Norman origin): variant of   Cumming  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Common","meanings":["nickname from Middle English <i>comen</i>, Old English <i>cuman</i> ‘guest, stranger, newcomer’.","variant of   Cumming  .","English:"]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Cumming was born about 1300, in Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom as the daughter of Cumming Lord of the Braes of Lochaber. She married John - Iain Dubh mac Gilliemore MacLean 1st of Duart, 4th of Clan MacLean about 1323, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"about 1300–":"umbes 1300–Surnud","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1280–1330":"1280–1330","1324–1405":"1324–1405","1330–1408":"1330–1408","–Male":"Surnud","1324":"1324","1300":"1300","about 1323":"umbes 1323","1330":"1330","about 1300":"umbes 1300","about 1330":"umbes 1330","1408":"1408","1280":"1280","1405":"1405","Knapdale, Argyll, Scotland":"Knapdale, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Argyll, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Lochbuie, Argyll, Scotland":"Lochbuie, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1300–":"noin 1300–Kuollut","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1280–1330":"1280–1330","1324–1405":"1324–1405","1330–1408":"1330–1408","–Male":"Kuollut","1324":"1324","1300":"1300","about 1323":"noin 1323","1330":"1330","about 1300":"noin 1300","about 1330":"noin 1330","1408":"1408","1280":"1280","1405":"1405","Knapdale, Argyll, Scotland":"Knapdale, Argyll, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Argyll, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lochbuie, Argyll, Scotland":"Lochbuie, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1300–":"environ